A 37- year- old man, Mutiu Sonola, has been arrested by operatives of the Ogun State Police Command for allegedly beating his 34-year- old wife, Zainab Shotayo, to death on Christmas day. Daily Independent gathered that the suspect was arrested on December 25 2019 following a report by the father of the deceased, who complained at Ibara division that he was called on phone that his daughter was having a misunderstanding with her husband and that she has been beaten into coma by the husband. Confirming the incident, Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) Abimbola Oyeyemi, the Ogun State Police Command spokesman, said the father of the deceased said he he quickly raced to the scene and her daughter was taken to the to General Hospital, Ijaye, where the doctor confirmed her dead. “As soon as the suspect realised that the victim was dead, he took to his heels. On the strength of the report, the DPO Ibara Division, Superintendent of Police (SP) Dada Olusegun, mobilised his detectives and went after the suspect. His hiding place was eventually located and he was promptly arrested. “Preliminary investigation revealed that the man is fond of beating the deceased at any slight provocation and that the incident of that fateful day was a very minor disagreement. “The corpse of the deceased has been deposited at general hospital mortuary for autopsy. “Meanwhile, the Commissioner of Police, (CP) Kenneth Ebrimson, has ordered the immediate transfer of the suspect to Homicide Section of the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department (SCIID) for further investigation and prosecution.